<br>
#1<br>
In the Grand Bazaar, you think people will take their time going about life. I mean, most people just sit and stand around waiting for someone to purchase their wares.  You would THINK, someone would notice the lid of a barrel being missing over the course of a few days wouldn't you?  Most people would not consider this small thing a problem, BUT for us shorties trying to get in better view to sell wares... it becomes a LARGE problem.  It seems that our tiny little bodies will fit PERFECTLY into these cruel torture chambers others call barrels.  We fit so darn perfectly that it creates a suction problem and our little bodies cannot escape without assistance!!  The horror... the pain... of being stuck in a wooden tomb just being able to spin in circles screaming in agony!  Anyway, thanks to a VERY generous nearby Shaman... my body was made to grow in form and the suction hold was broken!  Thank goodness for me and thanks to the ill-remembered Shammy!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
#2<br>
Once, whilst exploring some new areas in this grand world and others linked to it.  I found a very neat place called ShadowHaven.  It is a GRAND place with many long underground halls... even those Brell would be darn proud of.  I arrived their by mistake actually, and was so happy to find it.  After wandering around for a while and actually finding a spell I could not get elsewhere... I decided to head homeward.  From what I was told, I just had to get back to the place I arrived from.  This was an easy task since I have a good memory for travel... as us Gnomads do.  This is where I found my second problem!  It seems, that no matter how nice the little pool of water surrounding the teleport area looks, it is NOT made for swimming in!  I mean, I had walked a lot and my clockwork armor seemed to need a washing.  A washing it GOT!  For once in the small clean pool... I could not escape it's purely icy-clutches!!  I would sit and watch as other BIG races would jump in and jump out at will... but I hardly had enough energy to stay afloat!  I removed me armor...yet still could not reach the HIGH walls on the side of it!  Have you ever tried to tread water and scream for help at the same time... horrible I say... horrible!!!  I understand if there was a sign that said &quot;Gno swimming allowed&quot;, but was there.... NOOOOO!  Once again... my screams were heard by a VERY kind and generous Shaman that made me big and strong.  I was able to easily step out of that evil water-pit after that.  Whew... the price I pay to sometimes become a better swimmer and keep from smelling!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh well, that is all the time I have currently my short friends.  Please feel free to add to my list as you see fit.  I hope this gives others some insight into the life they might find crazy at times.  Have a good day and keep exploring little ones!!<br>
<br>
Comitas - The Semi-master Swimmer and Barrel-Hider!<br>
